PRETORIA, South Africa, August 27, 2018/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            The Statistician-General of South Africa, Risenga Maluleke, will release the Recorded live births, 2017 report at a media briefing to be held on Monday, 27 August 2018 in Pretoria.



The Recorded live births report presents information on live births in South Africa, based on data from the national birth registration system. The report also provides data on the number of registered live births, number of live births by age of the mother, and birth registration trends between 1995 and 2017, amongst others.

The media briefing will be held as follows:

Date: Today, 27 August 2018

Time: 11:00

Venue: Tshedimosetso House, Cnr Francis Baard & Festival streets, Hatfield, Pretoria.